<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - REMOVE - AUXILIARY DRIVE
        GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303240">Figure 40</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1303240" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303240.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 40. Auxiliary Drive Gear Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring at the rear of the mainshaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303241">(Figure 41</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the auxiliary drive gear off the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303241">Figure 41).</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six (6) auxiliary bearing retainer ring bolts and bearing retainer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303241">Figure 41)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303241" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303241.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 41. Removing Auxiliary Drive Gear Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert one (1) large screwdriver into the front section gearing. Use the screwdriver to
                slide the mainshaft and mainshaft rear bearing rearward
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303242">(Figure 42)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a rolling head prybar (crow's foot) to work the mainshaft rear bearing out of the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303243">Figure 43</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the bearing must be replaced, press the inner spacer from the mainshaft rear bearing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303242" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303242.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 42. Slide Mainshaft Rear Bearing Rearward</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1303243" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303243.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 43. Remove Mainshaft Bearing Out Of Bore</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
